Angola Replaces Energy and Water Minister, State News Says

-- B y   C o l i n   M c C l e l l a n d
-- 
2011-12-01T17:42:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/angola-replaces-energy-and-water-minister-state-news-says.html
Angola ,  Africa ’s second-largest crude
producer, named Joao Baptista Borge as minister of energy and
water, Angola Press, the southwest African country’s state-owned
news agency, reported, citing a note from the presidency.  President Jose Eduardo dos Santos dismissed Emanuela
Bernardeth Afronso Vieria Lopes, Angola Press said on its
 website . No reason was given.  The government’s oil industry is overseen by Jose Maria Botelho de Vasconcelos, the minister of petroleum.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Colin McClelland in Toronto at   cmcclelland1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 